title: Baking Bonanza
overview:
Baking Bonanza
    
        Play Baking Bonanza demo game online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. No download required.
about_game: Run your own Yorkshire tea house in this baking themed Slingo machine with an RTP of 96.47% and medium volatility.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Baking Bonanza is all about putting together delicious desserts, presenting you with an array of tasty treats to cook up as you play.
The game uses a bingo-style system to allow you to choose your own recipes (win conditions) and to collect the necessary ingredients (symbols).
If you’re a fan of the Great British Bakeoff or you just enjoy a little bit of homemade confectionary, this might scratch your itchy sweet-tooth.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The slot is beautifully designed with a central appearance that owes much to the decor of English high-street tea rooms. The pastel coloured background and bright cakes, rendered in a clean dessert menu style, make for a charming atmosphere.
The tone of the slot is controlled by an excellent soundscape that starts with a jolly theme tune and ambient cooking noises, and works its way down to the detailed sounds which make up the win and spin sounds.
The animations are fairly simple, but they enhance the detailed and varied artwork, and work nicely with the sounds. Overall, this slot has a wonderfully designed front-end.

media.caption: You can continue spinning even after you achieve a winning combination

Gameplay.text:
Baking Bonanza uses the Slingo system. This is a cross between slots and bingo. Players select a series of "recipes," each of which is made up of a series of "ingredients." Each recipe has a different payout, which is based on how difficult the combination of ingredients is to get.
The ingredients make up the symbols on the reels. A player collects ingredients when they appear on the five slots of the single reels.
Collecting all the ingredients for a recipe leads to a payout. The player receives five spins for their first wager. After that, they can either reset the reels, or continue, paying an additional amount for each subsequent spin.
The wager amount is adjusted by the software to ensure a uniform RTP.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text: Because of the unusual game format, Baking Bonanza doesn’t have a Bonus system nor does it make use of Wilds.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.47%, comfortably over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€1.00 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. The player can increase volatility somewhat by choosing higher paying recipes, which can make the game somewhat more suitable for our slot strategies.

media.caption: High paying symbols in the Baking Bonanza slot

Conclusion.text:
Baking Bonanza is a very pretty slot. It is stylish and executes its theme perfectly. Animations, art, and music are all on point.
The unusual gameplay won’t appeal to everyone, but if you’re looking for a little variety in your slot experience, it can’t hurt to roll in some Slingo-based offerings.
The RTP is solid, though we’d prefer a higher volatility game for strategic reasons, but if you’re not too worried about that, this is a good slot in most other ways.

title: Book of Shadows
overview:
Book of Shadows
    
        Play Book of Shadows demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This medium RTP (96.01%), high volatility gothic horror slot is full of spooky delights.

Theme and Storyline.text:
This slot has a gothic horror theme.
Set in misty haunted woods, this game is filled with eerie characters and mystic symbols. Players will feel like they’ve entered a world of Halloween intrigue as they collect strange artifacts.
Despite the spooky mood, the atmosphere still feels playful in this ghostly forest. Players will enjoy leaning into their inner goth as they take part in the supernatural adventure.

media.caption: Big win in the Book of Shadows slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The tension-inducing soundtrack is filled with creepily tinkling bells. Wolf howls and owl hoots occasionally punctuate the music, adding to the feeling that players are lost in a mysterious forest.
Symbols such as an eyeball in a bottle and an emblematic moth suggest the ingredients for magic potions. Meanwhile, a sprightly cat swishes its tail right out its reel like a tiny whip.
Most iconic, though, is a pale-eyed girl with black tears streaming down her face. She seems to know more than she’s letting on as she mischievously smirks.
The gently flowing mist in the background makes the atmosphere immersive and gives the uneasy feeling that it won’t be easy to find a way out of these woods.

media.caption: One of the two gamble features in the game

Gameplay.text:
Book of Shadows is a five reel slot with between three and five rows depending on players’ preference. The top two rows are kept under shadows unless the player ups their bet to unveil them.
The game has up to 20 win lines depending on how many rows players opt to play with.
Players will have the option to use one of two gamble options, the first of which works like a double or nothing game. The second is a wheel of fortune-style game in which players can win free spins.
At the end of a spin, players have the option to pay extra to lock one or more of the reels in place for their next spin.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols. It also functions as a Scatter symbol, triggering the Free Spin Bonus when 3 or more land anywhere on the reels.
Players start the Free Spin Bonus with 10 free spins.
While in the Free Spins feature, a symbol is selected at random to become an expanding symbol. During the free spins, this symbol expands to fill the reel whenever it lands.
The Free Spin Bonus can be retriggered.

media.alt: Book of Shadows & Free spins options
media.caption: Player can shuffle expanding symbol or change the number of rows for the bonus feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.01%, almost exactly our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100 per spin if the player has three rows active. The maximum bet can go as high as $/£/€200 per spin if the player has all five rows active.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for the Book of Shadows slot machine

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this medium RTP, high volatility gothic-themed slot. The engrossing atmosphere and playful animation makes this game an entertaining experience.
It is no surprise that this game has achieved high popularity with its varied bonus options and engaging gameplay.
Many players will enjoy the great degree of control they have over their gameplay experience with this slot's many customisable features.
Players vying for optimised winnings may wish to move on to games with somewhat higher RTPs, but even they will enjoy a stop in this haunted world.

title: Rosh Immortality Cube Megaways
overview:
Rosh Immortality Cube Megaways
    
        Play Rosh Immortality Cube Megaways demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Enter a beautiful fantasy world in search of the immortality cube in this high volatility slot with an RTP of 96.15%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Rosh Immortality Cube is set in an original fantasy realm. On one side, the forces of evil preside over a brutally ravaged land, on the other, the forces of light protect what is left of nature. In between is the sorcery Rosh who draws his power from a mysterious artefact known as the Cube.
The Cube appears on the reels from time to time to trigger features, making the story an integral part of the mechanics of the game.
From the few details and character art on the reel, players can get an excellent sense of a rich world full of magical beings and powerful races.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics for Rosh Immortality Cube are awesome. The characters are rendered in a full 1990s fantasy novel cover art-style, but each character has benefited from the two to three decades of computer game character design in the intervening years.
The animations are extensive. In the background, light beams move and a crackling orb of magical energy sparks. The reels are animated with a feeling of weight in the spins, a feeling that is amplified by clever use of sound effects and music.

media.caption: Base game win in the Rosh Immortality Cube slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Rosh Immortality Cube is built using the Megaways system.
This uses six reels. Each spin, the number of symbols on each reel is randomised to between two and seven. This is coupled with an any way wins system.
This means that winning combinations are formed by matching symbols in adjacent reels starting from reel one. The Megaways combination of randomised row numbers and any way wins payouts results in between 128 and 117,649 ways to win for each spin.
The Megaways system uses cascades. This means winning combinations are removed from the reels, new symbols drop down from above, and any new wins are calculated. This continues until there are no new wins and the spin ends.
Rosh Immortality Cube also sports a variety of bonuses to keep things interesting.
The overall result of this is a fast paced and constantly engaging style of gameplay.

media.caption: Big win in the Rosh Immortality Cube slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols in the base game except the Scatter symbol.
Three Scatters anywhere on the reels during a single spin trigger one of three bonuses: the Mystery Multiplier Bonus, Mystery Cube Bonus, or Mystery Ways Bonus.
The Mystery Multiplier Bonus simply pays out a randomised multiple of the player's bet. The Mystery Cube Bonus adds 12 mystery cubes that transform into random symbols, giving the player another shot at making winning combos for free. The Mystery Ways Bonus gives the player three free spins with each spin having an increasing number of win ways (controlled by the number of symbols per reel).
The big bonus is the Free Spin Bonus. This is triggered by landing four or more Scatter symbols on one spin.
Free Spins use a completely new set of reels made up entirely of multipliers and blanks.
At the end of the Free Spins, the player receives a payout equal to the total of the multipliers added together. If the player lands a Mystery Cube during the free spins, the cube transforms into one of three symbols: Mystery Double which doubles all the multipliers on the reels at that time, Mystery Collect which collects all the multipliers on the reel and adds them to its total, and Mystery Removal which removes the lowest multipliers without affecting the player’s total and thereby freeing space up for further symbols to land.
Players can buy directly into the Free Spin Bonus.

media.caption: Free Spins consist of multipliers and blanks

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game 96.15%, a touch over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€.0.40 up to a maximum of $/£/€200.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Rosh Immortality Cube slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Rosh Immortality Cube has a certain appeal right off the bat thanks to its stats. High volatility and an above average RTP make it ideal for our preferred strategies.
When this is coupled with a set of graphics and gameplay mechanics as sophisticated and engrossing as this one, it thrills us no end.
We highly recommend this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Emperor’s Diamonds crosses two classic slot themes.
The first is the classic red-and-gold Chinese theme. As you would expect, this theme has a vague orientalist feel. The reels have symbols that are coins with square holes in the middle and red envelopes.
The second theme is the jewel theme. Simple crystals to play symbols in a gambling game makes a kind of natural sense. The combination appears in the design of those symbols, where the jewels are carved into animals from the Chinese zodiac. There are sapphire fish, ruby dragons, and emerald elephants.
The theme is a neat way of recombining familiar things to make something fresh and original.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Emperor’s Diamond has a pleasant visual style. The symbols have a 3D feel to them, but work nicely on the grid of the reels. They are all easily identifiable and attractively drawn. The various jewel-like animals are pretty to look at and all have clear silhouettes.
The animations are not especially imaginative. But, again, they are done with obvious professionalism.
The soundtrack is a well chosen loop of music that fits the theme and doesn’t tire by repetition. Sound effects aren’t flashy, but they also fit in nicely with the atmosphere of the slot.
The whole thing is a testament to how effective it can be to just get the fundamentals right, even if you don’t do anything too fancy with them.

Gameplay.text:
Emperor’s Diamonds base game is a five reel slot. It sports three rows per reel, and 30 non-adjustable win lines.
The Bonus elements (details below) are made up of Free Spins and a Jackpot. The free spins use a different set of reels.
There is no gamble feature.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter and Bonus symbols.
The Scatter pays for three or more symbols anywhere on the reels. This also triggers eight free spins for the player.
Six or more Bonus symbols anywhere on the reels will trigger the Diamond Bonus. The reels change so that the only symbols on the reels are Bonus symbols and blanks. The player then gets three respins.
The Bonus symbols stay in place while the reels are respun. Respins reset to three whenever new Bonus symbol appears in the corner of the grid. When all four corners are filled, reels expand to a new setting. This goes through grids 6x3 and 6x4 up to the final size of 8x4. During the Diamond Bonus feature, all Bonus symbols have a randomised value of between 1 and 50 times the player’s bet per spin. These values are raised to the range of 3 and 250 in the final 8x4 grid. There are also symbols with the names of each of the four Jackpots.
At the end of the respins, the player is awarded the total on all the Bonus symbols they accrued.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Gods of Gold has for its theme a kind of adventure-serial version of comparative theology. The reels are adorned with golden idols. Some evoke ancient Greece, others ancient China, others the Incas, still others the gods of Egypt.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:

Gameplay.text:
Gods of Gold uses a gameplay system called Infinireels. The base game starts out as a three reel, three row slot. And it uses an any way wins system. This means that winning combinations are made by the same symbol anywhere in adjacent reels going from the leftmost reel.
What makes the Infinireels system different is that when a winning combo lands, an additional reel is added to the right hand side of the slot. There is no upper limit for how many reels the player can end up with.
When a reel finally drops that doesn’t add to a winning combo, the spin ends and the player's winnings are calculated.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Gold Volcano is set on the harrowing sides of an almighty volcano. Above the mountain, the sky is red with the infernal glow of lava, while the way ahead is studded with precious stones thrown up by the eruption (the symbols on the reels are gems).
Below the reels, the player can see the boiling magma swirling through a cross-section of the mountain.
Players must struggle their way towards the peak, or risk being swallowed up in fire.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Gold Volcano sports some fun graphics. The grid of jewels is pretty basic, but it is animated well and the symbols are good enough for the job.
The design elements that shine are the simple but effective use of the background. This is an atmospheric depiction of a volcano, and as cascades occur, the lava is animated to rise, filling the cone with magma, getting closer and closer to eruption.
The music is a tense movie style soundtrack. The spin sounds have a weighty feel and sound like rocks being moved about by the rumbling earth.
The design elements are simple but effective and all come together to make a thrilling atmosphere for the game.

Gameplay.text:
Volcano Gold uses a grid style system. In this system, winning combinations are formed by groups of four or more identical symbols which are in contact vertically or horizontally.
Symbols rise up from the bottom. When a winning combination lands, it is removed from the reels and new symbols rise to take their place. The cascade system also serves to trigger the free spin bonus after six cascades.
The base game has three randomly triggered features that mix things up for the player. These are: Rumble, in which symbols are shaken into new position and a Scatter is added to the reels; Lava, in which in which an additional layer is added to the reel, all of the same symbol; and Excavate, which adds three to five random Wilds to the reels.
There are a couple of other bonus features, described in fuller detail below, that keep the slot’s gameplay interesting, varied, and fast paced.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Wilds appear at random when a winning combination is removed. They can come with a multiplier that is applied to any win that involves that particular Wild.
If the player gets six cascades on one spin, they trigger the Free Spin bonus. This begins at five free spins.
During the free spins, the grid is enlarged to an eight by eight grid. If the player gets another six cascades during the free spins, they receive an additional spin.
Hitting three Scatter symbols in a spin will result in one of the Amethyst symbols on the board being turned into Gold symbols, the highest value symbol. Three more on the same spin will do the same for the Ruby symbols. Three more and the Emerald symbols follow suit. This can result in huge payouts.
During Free Spins, the Scatter meter does not reset between spins.

about_game: This visually striking and utterly charming slot combines cutesy monsters and smart Wilds into a high volatility slot with an RTP of 96.20%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The Reactoonz franchise is built around a mix of cartoon monsters many of which have quirky effects on the base gameplay. Reactoonz 2 is thematically very similar to the first one, most of the changes are under the hood in the more complex gameplay.
But for anyone new to the franchise, the little blob-like aliens should be enough to charm you into enjoying the strange and wonderful world they inhabit.

media.caption: Big wins usually follow filling the Quantumeter to level 3 or 4

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are one of the key selling points for this Play'n GO's slot. Though they are by no means the only one. All the symbols are tiny aliens, each of which are given as much unique personality as can be crammed into such simple limbless creatures.
The various parts of the screen are all fully animated. The background is a swirling vortex of space colours, the indices around the main reels are surrounded by crackling electricity, glowing lights, or moving meters. The effect is one of constant action, especially once the reels kick off with their complex dance of features and symbols.
The music is a little repetitive in a way that grinds, but the other sound effects are so numerous and charming that unless players leave the game idle on their screens, they shouldn’t have any trouble with it.

Gameplay.text:
Reactoonz 2 expands on the gameplay of the previous iteration of the series. The reels make up a seven by seven grid. Any group of five or more symbols connected horizontally or vertically is a winning group. The bigger the group, the bigger the win.
A cascade feature means that any winning combination is removed from the reels while more symbols drop down from above to replace them.
After each cascade, new winning combinations can be made and removed. If this happens, it triggers another cascade.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are three kinds of Wild symbols. The Charged Wild, Energoon Wild, and Electric Wild all substitute for all other symbols. The main difference is in how they come to be on the reels.
An additional symbol, the Uncharged Wild can become an Electric Wild if next to a winning combination or if a Wild pair explosion goes off. Uncharged Wilds appear at random during regular spins. All other Wilds are awarded as part of the bonus systems.
The first bonus system is the Fluctometer which is assigned a random one-eyed monster every spin. If the player gets eleven of that monster in winning combinations that spin, the Fluctometer reaches full charge and adds one, two, or three Electric Wilds to the reels.
Each winning symbol that is part of a group with an Electric Wild adds one "charge" to the other meter: the Quantumeter. The Quantumeter has three levels. Over 55 charges activates level one, releasing four Energoon Wilds onto the reels. If the player gets over 85 charges, then the player gets a 2x2 Energoon Wild.
If the player gets the Quantumeter to level 3, they get a Gargantoon Wild added to the grid. Level 3 triggers a single 3x3 Gargantoon Wild. There is also an extra level 4, which adds a x2 multiplier to all Gargantoon Wins.
After each cascade is finished, the Gargantoon Wild breaks up into first two 2x2 Wilds, then nine 1x1 Wilds. This makes for huge wins and is more or less the equivalent of a Bonus Feature in other games.

media.caption: Neighbouring Electic Wild symbols explode after the last cascade, leaving ony Wild symbols behind.
Level 3 on Quantumeter awards the 3x3 Gargantoon Wild symbol

Theme and Story Line.text:
Cash Volt takes the classic iconography of old-style slot machines and transforms it into a retro gameshow scoreboard. The lighting, colour scheme, and arrangement of the various meters and buttons are all designed to evoke shows like Who Wants To Be A Millionaire and Mastermind. But with added electricity.
The style works pretty well, even though the gameplay mechanics of a slot are wholly different to a gameshow. Somehow those two worlds never stop colliding.

media.caption: Standard symbols win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are pretty enough. The background and symbols aren’t complicated, but the artists have rendered them realistically.
The whole thing is animated in a similar manner. Without much in the way of imagination, but plenty of competence on display.
Cash Volt has a funky disco soundtrack with a strong 70s vibe, but updated for the electronic age. The win and spin sounds are a bit basic but they work with the overall tone. The buzzing of electricity as sparks fly is very on theme.

Gameplay.text:
Cash Volt is a five reel slot, with three rows and twenty win lines. So, a pretty standard setup. Nothing too electrifying here so far.
Most of the quirks of gameplay are in the Cash Volt Bonus (details below). It provides enough variety to keep things going at a decent pace.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Cash Volt doesn’t have a Wild symbol or conventional bonuses. It does have a Scatter though.
Six or more Scatters anywhere on the reels pay out a multiple of the player's bet per spin. The more Scatters the player hits, the more they get paid. Six Scatters will win x5 the player's bet, Seven Scatters wins x15. Meanwhile the lucky player that fills all fifteen spots on the reels with Scatter symbols will win x2,500.
There are no free spins, so the Scatter payouts serve as close to bonuses as this game has.

media.alt: Cash Volt with Scatter Big win
media.caption: Big win with 8 Scatter symbols

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.71%, a little under our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€20.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a bad match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

Conclusion.text:
Generally speaking, a low RTP is bad news for a slot, and while Cash Volt does a nice job with the visual style, there’s not enough to like about the slot to make up for the 4.29% vig.
The bonuses and gameplay are pretty basic. They are solid, but lack sufficient flare to make up for the downsides of this slot.
We do not recommend Cash Volt highly.

title: Gonzos Quest Megaways
overview:
Gonzos Quest Megaways
    
        Play Gonzos Quest Megaways demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Trek into the jungle with Gonzo, the conquistador. Hunt for gold in Aztec ruins, just bear in mind the RTP is relatively low (95.77%) on this one.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Gonzo’s Quest is a classic slot in which Gonzo, a conquistador, must hunt through Inca treasures with the player. Here, that classic is given the Megaways overhaul.
The theme remains mostly the same with Gonzo in the bottom left encouraging the player or sympathising with their disappointment. The setting is similar with the wall of Aztec art making up the reels and the deep, impenetrable jungle surrounding both the reels and Gonzo.
Whether Gonzo gets out of that jungle with anything to show for it is down to the trio of Lady Luck, the Amazon jungle, and the player.

media.alt: Gonzo's Quest Megaways max multiplier win
media.caption: High chance of a big win if player reaches the top multiplier

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The Gonzo’s Quest slot was a pretty one even before the makeover to work with the Megaways system. The slot’s visuals shine, with the 3D rendering of Gonzo and his environs jumping out of the screen. The reels are a wall of Aztec symbols carved in stone, a fact which is beautifully emphasised by the sound effects.
The music is a tribal set of percussion sounds, along with some ambient jungle sounds to give things some atmosphere.
Everything is neatly animated. Nothing too flashy, but all solid and detailed with a good sense of timing and weight. Gonzo himself is fully animated, but as he’s small and kept to one side, he isn’t too distracting.

Gameplay.text:
Gonzo’s Quest Megaways uses the Megaways system for its reels. This is an any way wins system that randomises the number of symbols per reel.
"Any way wins" means that winning combinations are formed by matching symbols anywhere on consecutive reels starting from the leftmost reel. The randomised symbols means each reel can have between two and seven symbols, making for up to 117,649 ways to win.
A cascade system removes winning symbols. New symbols then drop down from above, and any new wins are calculated. Each cascade increases the multiplier. The multiplier then resets when the spin ends.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols including the Free Spin symbol. Additionally, Wilds do not get removed during the destruction phase of the cascade.
The Free Spin symbols, unlike many slots, are not Scatters. The player must land three or more in the same manner as a regular symbol to trigger the free spins.
The free spin bonus starts at 9 free spins for three Free Spin symbols. The player is awarded an additional +3 spins for each Free Spin symbol over three. During the free spins, the cascade multipliers increase. The first win has a multiplier of x3 applied to it. Subsequent cascades get x6, x9, x15 with all cascades after that getting the x15 multiplier applied.

media.caption: A bonus feature that destroys all low paying symbols in the current spin

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.77%, a little below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€4.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is at the high end of medium, which would make it a reasonable match for our preferred slot machine strategies if the RTP were a bit more impressive. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility and RTP.

media.caption: Full paytable for Gonzo's Quest Megaways slot machine

Conclusion.text:
The RTP is a little low. Though the volatility is a lot closer to what we would want, together they just don’t work all that well with our preferred strategies.
However, in most other ways, this is a top notch slot and the popularity of the Gonzo’s Quest franchise is unsurprising. The graphics are excellent, the world-building is on point, and Gonzo himself is a fun little cartoon avatar for the player to relate to.
The bonuses aren’t mind-blowing, but they provide nice variety and the cascade system keeps the pacing of gameplay engaging.
If you aren’t too worried about the vig, this is a solid slot.

about_game: Infinity Hero ends up being anything but heroic with its prosaic visuals and typical gameplay.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Infinity Hero is based around its own original superhero. Rendered in the style of old pulp comics, Infinity Hero doesn’t do a lot of heroic things during the course of the game.
Mostly Infinity Hero, the character, stands around, and if the player doesn’t spin the reels, he gets increasingly annoying. He yawns, picks up his phone, or tells the player to hurry up.
The reels feature basic one-armed bandit symbols but rendered in a comic book style. For such a visually excellent slot, much more could have been made of the theme.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Infinity Reel has an impressive visual style. It is a bright, stylised version of old-fashioned comic-book print, with the outlines and colours being slightly misaligned. However, having gone to the trouble of creating a cool look for the slot, the design team seems to have given up. The symbols are just fruit machine symbols. The background is just a basic city skyline. The hero of the title is mostly off screen.
When he is on screen, he is well animated. So are the win and spin movements. But without something interesting to apply all that movement to, the slot feels flatter than the page it pretends to be printed on.
The soundtrack is also pretty basic. The music is a vaguely cinematic loop. There are simple win and spin sounds that could have been used for any slot. Again, this is strange as the designer bothered to record a voice actor delivering Infinity Hero’s lines, but didn’t spring for a few more interesting sound loops.

media.caption: Base game win in the Infinity Hero slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Infinity Hero is played on a grid of six reels. There are three rows and twenty win lines on these reels. The win lines are non-adjustable.
There is a simple, double-or-nothing feature which players can use to up their volatility at the end of a spin.
The Free Spin Bonus (details below) is pretty standard fare. Overall, the gameplay is very average, certainly not super.

media.caption: Big win in the Infinity Hero slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Three or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reel will trigger the free spin bonus.
During the Free Spin bonus, there are additional symbols added to the reel. There are three of these, each one has a picture of a bomb and the number three, five, or seven. Landing one of these Bomb symbols will add the number to the total number of free spins the player gets.
Each time the player wins during the Free Spin bonus, a multiplier increases by one. The multiplier starts at x1. The multiplier is applied to each win as it happens.

media.caption: During Free Spins, the multiplier starts at x1 and increases by 1 with each win

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.24%, just over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is adjustable. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility, so we recommend setting the volatility to high.

media.caption: High paying symbols of the Infinity Hero slot machine

Conclusion.text:
The RTP and adjustable volatility are nice features here.
However, the slot itself manages to be very boring from an overall design standpoint, and deeply uninspiring at the gameplay level.
The game is not offensively bad, but it doesn’t get an active recommendation from us.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Football Glory does its best to recreate some of the thrill of watching your favourite teams and players compete for a gold trophy. With its background of a football pitch and atmospheric sounds of cheering crowds, the game puts you in the stands watching the action unfold.
There are four players, each of who represents a different team. They run the gamut from stylish young guns to skinhead head thugs.
Fans of football aren’t short of gambling opportunities, but here’s yet another.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Football Glory is an Yggdrasil Gaming slot, which means two things: gorgeous graphics and clever gameplay. While Yggdrasil might have let the ball slip through their goalie gloves a little on this one, it's not a bad looking slot.
The field in the background sets the scene nicely and the symbols all work well with the theme and style of the slot.
The real masterstroke, though, is the soundtrack. A dull roar of a stadium crowd creates the ambient track, while understated win and spin sounds work together to build the feel of a stadium at capacity.

media.caption: Win in the Football Glory slot

Gameplay.text:
The basic gameplay is pretty simple. A five reel slot with four rows and 25 win lines making up the main game.
The really interesting parts of the gameplay lie in the bonuses (details below). These combine to make an exciting, well paced game.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Cup symbols and Free Spin symbols.
There are two Cup symbols. In the base game, landing the Silver Cup symbol or a Gold Cup symbol during a spin allows the player to draw one of five prizes. The prizes for the Silver Cup are a payout of a randomised multiple of the player's bet, or free spins.
The Gold Cup also awards a randomised multiple of the player's bet or free spins, but the range of prizes is higher for the Gold Cup than for the Silver. You can also win additional bonus games and features with a Gold Cup.
Landing a Cup symbol during free spins awards players with additional free spins or extra Wilds.
The Free Spin bonus is triggered one of two ways.
The first way is by filling up a footballer’s meter. Each time a footballer symbol is part of a winning combo, that footballer’s meter increases. Filling the meter triggers Superstar Free Spins, in which that footballer’s symbol becomes a sticky Wild whenever one lands.
The second way is to hit three or more Free Spin symbols. The more Free Spin symbols you hit, the more free spins are awarded. During these free spins, the footballer symbols all play as in the base game. None become sticky Wilds. However, some will become regular Wilds at random.
Before Free Spins a wheel is spun which can award additional spins, Superstar Free Spins, sticky Wilds, or a Wild reel.

media.caption: Landing a Golden Cup offers the chance to pick 1 of the 5 prizes

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.10%, right in the range of "roughly 96%" which we consider average.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€125.00 per spin.

media.caption: High paying symbols in the Football Glory slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Football Glory is the ideal slot for any soccer fans who just can’t leave the game behind on the pitch. The graphics are good and the sense of atmosphere excellent.

We can give this one a light recommendation.

about_game: Wild Pops combines clever gameplay with gorgeous visuals to charm players. Unfortunately, the volatility is lower than we would like.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Wild Pops is set in a Kung Fu Panda style world where animals and Eastern mythology meet. As you might expect from an Yggdrasil Gaming slot, the detail put into the world is remarkable, and care has been taken to create a set of interesting and unique characters rendered in a style that is wholly particular to this one slot.
The characters include a pig in imperial garb, a cheeky crow with a coin in his mouth, and a furious green dragon. Each is rendered in an art style that echoes both Chinese statuary and Pixar animations.
It is a beautiful fantasy world.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Wild Pops is a visual delight. The characters are absolutely brimming with character, but all conform to the visual style of the slot.
The animations are detailed and relatively long. Each one gives the character a little more individuality and helps build a world that immerses the player as they spin the reels.
The music is a little off-putting. It sounds like the kind of thing a spa might play in their massage room to relax the customers. There are a few East Asian instruments that creep in and out of the musical track, but it doesn’t quite fit the visual style in the way one imagines the composer was hoping.
It feels especially weird as the sound effects are bright and upbeat in striking contrast with the soothing musical track. Unfortunately, you can’t mute the music without muting the sound effects on this slot. It is the one weak point of an otherwise delightful set of audio-visual elements.

media.alt: Wild Pops slot super big win
media.caption: Super Big win in Yggdrasil's slot Wild Pops

Gameplay.text:
Wild Pops starts out as a five reel, three row slot. It uses an any way wins system to determine payouts. This means winning combinations start in reel one or reel five and are made up of matching symbols appearing anywhere in adjacent reels going in either direction.
When the player hits a winning combination, they trigger the Pops feature. The winning symbols are removed and replaced by two new random symbols. This increases the size of the reels and, because of the any way wins system, it also increases the number of ways to win. This continues until there are no new winning combinations.
Three cascades in a row has two Wilds added to the reels at random. Every 7th Pop increases the multiplier for that spin by one.
The reels return to three rows tall at the end of each spin.
It is a fun variation on the usual cascade system and marks out Wild Pops as especially interesting to play.

media.caption: 2 Wild symbols appear after every third cascade
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols.
If a reel gets to be seven symbols high thanks to the Pop reactions, then the play triggers the Bonus game.
The Bonus game begins with the player receiving three "lives". Each life triggers a respin when the respins would otherwise have ended. When the three lives are gone, the spin ends.

media.caption: Respin feature is awarded when all reels are 7 symbols high

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.2%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a rather weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Wild Pops top paying symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for highest paying symbols in the Wild Pops slot

Conclusion.text:
Wild Pops is an example of excellent slot design. The visuals are gorgeous and the gameplay fast paced and varied.
Our main gripe with the slot is that the volatility isn’t high enough to work with our preferred strategies and the RTP is only a little over average and so doesn’t make up for this fact.
If volatility is less of a worry for you as a slot-player, you will probably find this charming and fun slot well worth recommending.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Gorilla Gold takes players deep into the jungles of the world in search of rare and beautiful animals. Its quadruple reels sport the usual ace to ten symbols along with snakes, crocodiles, and tigers. A multi-continental menagerie of big game animals.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Gorilla Gold’s graphics are pretty solid. They are rendered nicely with a deep green background that allows the four reels in oranges and browns to really pop. The symbols are cool, dramatically drawn wildlife with a bit of a twist.
The animations are reasonable, highlighting action as it takes place and keeping things clear. The quadruple reels mean that unless you are playing on a large screen, the symbols can be a little small. The animations help with this.
The win and spin sounds are well chosen, and add nicely to the atmosphere of the slot. Though more thought could have been put into the limited musical accompaniment.

Gameplay.text:
In the base game there are four slot games. These play more or less independently. Remember to note that your bet per spin will be quadrupled as you are placing separate bets on each set of reels.
Each slot has six reels on which two to six symbols can appear. The number of symbols is randomised.
Winning combinations are formed by three or more matching symbols in adjacent reels starting from the leftmost reel. As a result, knock on effect of this, the number of win ways varies widely from spin to spin. Winning combos are removed from the reels, and new symbols drop down from above. This cascade feature works independently on each reel.
The bonus features are interesting (see below for detail) and, along with the cascade, keep the pace of the game constantly changing. Perfect for keeping players engaged.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
The Scatter symbol serves to trigger the Bonus. Three or more Scatters take the player to a wheel. Players spin the wheel to determine how many free spins they get, and whether those spins are Free Spins or Super Spins.
Free Spins take place on a single set of reels.
Super spins are only available to players who have activated the "Super Bet" option in the base game. During Super Spins, the player can collect Golden Gorillas. Five Golden Gorillas will activate a second set of reels. Fifteen Golden Gorillas will add another. At thirty Golden Gorillas, the player has all four slots in play.
The more Scatters that trigger the Bonus, the better the options on the wheel are. With four Scatters players can win either 20 Free Spins or 15 Super Spins. Each extra Scatter over four adds +5 to the possible number of either kind of spin.

Gorilla Gold Megaways makes excellent use of the Megaways system. By quadrupling it, the slot creates a very different feel that should keep players excited and interested from the start.
The graphics, animations, and soundtrack are all solid. Not the most thrilling set of designs, but competently put together, and it all works well with the interesting gameplay.
The main appeal for us is the combination of high volatility and high RTP. This makes Gorilla Gold Megaways an excellent slot for our slot strategies.

title: Book of Gates
overview:
Book of Gates
    
        Play Book of Gates demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This medium RTP (96.03%), high volatility slot provides pretty Egyptian aesthetics, but fails to enthrall.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Themed on ancient Egyptian lore, this game has a mystical atmosphere.
The slot is named after an ancient text which describes the passage of souls to the next world.
Players will find themselves at a gate guarded by an Egyptian god. Like the souls of the myth, they must undergo various tests before passing. Against an eerie sunset backdrop, players will search for patterns in the hieroglyphic-like symbols and hope to keep the gods on their side.
Mythology fans will enjoy being mesmerized by this esoteric world.

media.caption: Big win in the Book of Gates slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The haunting soundtrack is enjoyable and sets an underworld-tone. The gentle music remains undistracting and is, in fact, somewhat soothing. Players will feel as if they are at a particularly meditative spa.
Spins provoke a chiming. This enhances the sense that players are undergoing a mythical trial.
The desert sunset in the background is artfully rendered. It feels symbolic of the transition between worlds. The animation style of the gods and hieroglyphics emphasise fantasy rather than archaeology, but this is part of the fun.
The reels feel quite small. Players may prefer to play in the full-screen mode for a better view.
Overall, the front end is an aesthetically-pleasing fantasy world.

Gameplay.text:
Book of Gates is a five reel slot. Players will get between 2 and 5 symbols per reel column. This number is determined at random. There are three additional covered rows which feature in the Respins.
To win, players need to land adjacent symbols (from left to right), regardless of their size.  As a result, the base game offers up to 3,125 ways to win.
The three extra rows above the main gameplay area are uncovered bit by bit during Respins. Every time players hit a winning combination, they are given a Respin. Upon their first win, a row is unveiled, increasing the number of ways to win. This continues for the players second and third Respins until they have access to all of the rows.
Unfortunately, this basic gameplay doesn’t feel immersive, and players may have a hard time getting into the swing of it.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
The Wild symbol may only appear once per reel and will only appear on reels 2, 3, and 4. It will never appear on a reel at the same time as a Scatter symbol.
Only appearing in the base game, the Scatter symbol lands on reels 1, 3, and 5.
A set of 10 Free Spins are awarded when players land three Scatter symbols. Each reel will contain 5 to 8 symbols during the Free Spins round. This increases the number of ways to win up to 32,768.

media.alt: Book of Gates slot Respin feature

title: Animal Quest
overview:
Animal Quest
    
        Play Animal Quest demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Go on an adventure into a strange jungle where your companions are a menagerie of critters, an average RTP (96.11%), and high volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Animal Quest is set in a jungle where an ancient civilisation, not dissimilar to the Mayans, has left huge ruins for vines and undergrowth to smother in green.
The main difference between this jungle and one in our world is that here the explorers are non-human animals. The characters that the player explores the jungle with are a piratical opossum, a tech-wizard turtle, a rakish red panda, and a rhino with tribal tattoos.
The style is somewhere between Duck Tales and Indiana Jones.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The charming crew of explorers are drawn in a fun 
  cartoon style that makes the most of each creature’s features. Their symbols all ooze unique character and the lower paying symbols, which are mostly jungle artefacts, all display similar levels of cool in their execution.

media.alt: Animal Quest big win in Free spins
media.caption: Big symbols are multiplier Wilds in Free spins bonus

Gameplay.text:
The slot uses 40 paylines on a five reel, four row slot. The gameplay is fairly straightforward, without a gamble feature or complicated bonuses (see below for details on what bonuses there are).
Wins with a Big Symbol (one of the four animal characters) trigger a respin with the winning symbol becoming sticky.
But beyond that, the game isn’t looking to push the boat out in terms of innovative playing styles.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Two or more Scatters plus a Wild on one spin triggers ten free spins.
During the free spins, Big Symbols can land with a Gold outline. Gold symbols apply a multiplier to any wins they are part of. The Turtle is x2, the Rhino x3, the Opossum is x4, and the Red Panda is x5.

media.alt: Animal Quest slot Big symbol win
media.caption: Respin feature with the Big symbol in the base game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.11%, marginally above our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. Though we’d like higher RTP still, a roughly average RTP isn’t bad and couples well with the volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for Animal Quest slot machine

Conclusion.text:
At a simple mathematical level we like the high volatility of Animal Quest. It goes well with our slot strategies. The RTP is a little above average, but not by enough to make a fuss. But average ain’t bad. And the range of best on the site we tried allows players to meet the slot at whatever bankroll state they find themselves in.
You can add in that the gameplay is interesting enough to be fun, but isn’t gimmicky. And that all this is coupled with a stylish, fun, and immersive front end is just icing on the cake. Delicious, attractive icing.
We highly recommend this slot.

title: Hyper Burst
overview:
Hyper Burst
    
        Play Hyper Burst demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This high volatility, medium RTP (96%) slot is erupting with fantasy island fun.

Theme and Storyline.text:
With a Polynesian-flavour, this slot is full of volcanic eruptions.
The game is set in an island jungle, with wins taking the form of flowing lava. Players will be faced with an array of mysterious masks and etched letters. Like any adventurer, they will face the quest head on.
The references to Polynesian culture definitely feel more like a resort performance than an authentic portrayal. However, the colourful atmosphere keeps things light and fun.
Players looking for a warm, exotic fantasy will enjoy this game.

media.alt: Hyper Burst slot Super Big win
media.caption: Bigger wins are scarce in this highly volatile

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The music is theatrical with dramatic drums and mystical flutes. The reels spin with the sound of rumbling stones. Upon winning, the explosion of the volcano is extremely satisfying.
The mask symbols present a touristy impression of Polynsesian tribal art, but are eye-catching. Each mask has a unique colour and expression and their eyes glow on winning spins.
The highlight is the animation of the gushing lava that pours over the reels when the player wins. This creates a gratifying moment before the next spin.

Gameplay.text:
Hyper Burst is a six reel, four row slot, with twenty-five win lines.
When players win, this triggers the Respin mode. This means that two of the four middle reels combine to form two-by-two symbols. Further Respins increase the size of these blocks by one.
While in this mode, consecutive wins will prompt another Respin and trigger the lava reel to grow.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols. If the Wild symbols’ own payouts are worth more, this is activated instead.
During Respins, if the lava reel has grown to be four reels wide, Hyper Mode is activated.
The Hyper Mode begins by giving players a x2 Multiplier. Every consecutive win also gives players another Respin (this is unlimited). Meanwhile, the Multiplier can increase up to x10.
This serves as the game's only Bonus feature.

media.alt: Hyper Burst expanding reels & respin feature
media.caption: Each win awards a respin and the lava reel expands by one reel

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96%, exactly our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this volcano-themed game with medium RTP and high volatility that meshes well with our preferred strategies.
The steamy Polynesian setting is a great escape and the gushes of lava during Hyper Mode add showstopping drama.
Players will enjoy the colourful island world, and the engaging pace of gameplay.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The hosting elves have an inescapable creepy-doll vibe. Meanwhile, the playful animals among the symbols are simultaneously cute and unnervingly smiley.

The snow falling behind the reels is pretty and pleasant. It provides the illusion that the reels are panes of glass in a window.
The unobtrusive soundtrack is reminiscent of a music box. It fades easily into the background and players will be happy to leave it on.
Overall, players will need to be in the right headspace to enjoy this slot.

Gameplay.text:
Carol of the Elves is a five reel, five row slot.
Wins are given for landing three or more matching symbols on adjacent reels, starting from the left and going to the right. As a result, this slot offers 3,125 possible ways to win.
The reels have a number of blank squares called Blockers which can be added to the reels as part of the bonuses (details below).

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
This game does not include Wild symbols.
Players can win Magic Stars to destroy Blockers on the reels. The blockers take up positions on the reels, preventing symbols from landing. When all Blockers are destroyed, the player activates both Lantern Collections.
The Lantern Collections sit either side of the reels and monitor player’s progress towards Multipliers. Any subsequent wins while the Lantern Collections are unlocked will add lanterns to either the red or green counter.
When both Lantern Collections are activated players receive a x2 Win Multipliers. Players can also obtain +1 Multipliers every time 5 Green Lanterns are lit. Multipliers are applied to the next wins in a round.
Players can also receive +1 Extra life for every 5 Red Lanterns lit. This keeps the respins going even after a spin without a win.

Theme and Storyline.text:
If the idea of a white Christmas sounds a little too chilly for you, NetEnt have got you covered with this Hawaiian Christmas themed holiday in a slot. Enjoy fresh pineapples, cracked coconuts and Hawaiian hibiscus flowers on the reels.
Meanwhile in the background, beach bars and tiki statues are festooned with Santa hats and coloured lights.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are excellent. As well as iconic and easy to recognise symbols, the background is painted lovingly with an animated wooden statue who smiles, whistles, and plays the ukulele in the bonus games.
The style is upbeat and well animated, with bright background sounds and a fun soundtrack. Although the statue’s whistling can become a little annoying after a short while.
The other sound effects and animations are perfect for the setting, and make for a festive atmosphere with many delightful opportunities to enjoy the feeling of a Hawaiian holiday without the expense of going there.

Gameplay.text:
Aloha! Christmas is a cluster based slot. The symbols fall on a six-by-six grid. Clusters of nine or more symbols pay out. The larger the cluster, the bigger the payout. A cluster is defined by horizontal and vertical connections, not diagonals.
Unlike many cluster based slots, Aloha! Christmas does not sport a cascade function.
However, there are a number of stacked symbols and a mystery symbol feature to spice things up. There is also a free spin bonus to keep things spicy (see below for details of bonuses and features).
Additionally, winning clusters can randomly trigger respins. In this case the winning symbols are locked in place and the rest of the reels are respun. During respins, bigger clusters get higher multipliers added to them. This can make for some big wins.

media.caption: Big win in the Aloha! Christmas slot machine
One of the base game bonus features, the Sticky Win-respins

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
When Mystery symbols land on the reels, they turn into a randomly selected symbol. Additionally, one of them can turn into a Multiplier Wild, which substitutes for all symbols except the Free Spins symbol and also adds a multiplier to all winning combinations that include the Multiplier Wild.
Three or more Free Spin symbols anywhere on the reel will trigger the Free Spin bonus. It is worth noting that though the Free Spin symbol takes up two spaces on the reel, it only counts as one symbol.
More than three Free Spin symbols also add an instant cash prize to the player's wallet. The more symbols, the bigger the prize.
After triggering the Free Spin bonus, the player must choose between 10 free spins with Multiplier Wilds of x2, x3 and x4 or 6 free spins with Multiplier Wilds of x4, x5, and x7. We would recommend going with the higher variance option of fewer spins with higher multipliers, as increased volatility works well with our preferred strategies.

media.caption: Gameplay video
Choose between low and high volatility free spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.00%, right in the middle of our rough estimate for average.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€200.00 per spin. This makes for a substantial range of bets that covers the lowest bankroll to the highest rollers.
The volatility of this game is medium, an improvement on the non-holiday edition. Medium volatility doesn’t work brilliantly with our preferred slot machine strategies as our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Aloha! Christmas top paying symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for high paying symbols of the Aloha! Christmas slot

Conclusion.text:
Aloha! Christmas is a fun slot with some nice features. The grid-based reels make for a nice change as do the range of random and bonus features. Having a few of these in play keeps the slot from becoming too samey.
The RTP is okay and, although we’d prefer higher volatility, the bonus options mitigate that slightly. We’d probably not recommend this for those players who are sticking to our recommended strategies though.
Anyone else could have an absolute ball though.

Three Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels trigger the Free Games Feature.
The Free Games Feature begins when three or more Scatter symbols appear anywhere. Players will see the second and fourth reels filled by Mystery Stacks on their first spin. If there are additional Scatters, players are awarded +1 to the Free Games Feature, this moves the Mystery Stacks up one spot for each +1 awarded.
A Multiplier is also applied to each of the player’s wins. This Multiplier increases with each Nudge and Reveal Feature.
After each spin, the Mystery symbols move down by one space. The Free Games Feature continues until there are no Mystery symbols left on the reels. The Free Games Feature can therefore be extended by landing further Mystery symbols higher up on the reel.

When the Christmas Pie meter is full, the Fat Santa symbol increases in size, covering more squares on the reels. The more pies, the bigger your wins as the number of winning combos increases.
At random, the Santa’s Sleigh Feature begins, flying over the reels. Santa’s sleigh leaves a trail of Christmas Pie symbols in randomized positions. These symbols then act as Wild symbols.

title: Fruit Cocktail
overview:
Fruit Cocktail
    
        Play Fruit Cocktail demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This low RTP (94.39%), medium volatility fruit-themed slot has a classic vibe, but fails to stand out.

Theme and Style.text:
Fruit Cocktail has a classic fruit machine theme.
A smiling strawberry will welcome players to a world of ripe produce. Cherries, pears, peaches, and watermelons are all among the selection in this traditional slot world.
Players looking for a retro casino vibe will appreciate Fruit Cocktail.

media.caption: Win in the Fruit Cocktail slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Fruit Cocktail’s reels spin with a digital beeping sound effect that brings to mind classic slot machines. Meanwhile, the reels land with a satisfying clunk that adds a tactile feel.
The animation is of lower quality than most slots. The fruit symbols have minimal detail and the style is inconsistent with some figures outlined while others are not.
Fruit machine fans will spot many classic symbol types such as lemons, cherries, and watermelons. The symbols are displayed against grey reels that leave the atmosphere somewhat unfestive.
In front of the reels players will see a personified strawberry with green arms and legs. Although his smile is well-meaning, there is something uncanny about his expression.
Overall, the soundtrack and animation of Fruit Cocktail intend to create a classic fruit machine atmosphere, but produce a somewhat lackluster result.

Gameplay.text:
Fruit Cocktail is a five reel, three row slot, with 9 win lines. Players can opt to activate 1, 3, 5, 7, or all 9 win lines as they see fit.
This slot has a more moderate pace of gameplay which may make it more difficult for some players to remain engaged.

media.caption: Pick one of the cards in the gamble feature

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols with the exception of the Fruit Cocktail symbol.
Players have the option to bet their winnings by selecting the Gamble feature. Players will be prompted to pick a card from a selection of four facedown cards. In the event that their card is higher than the card of the dealer, their winnings will be doubled. However, their winnings will be entirely lost if they select a card that is lower than the dealer’s card.
Players are awarded 100x their total bet if they land the special Fruit Cocktail symbol.
If players land at least 3 Strawberry symbols, the Bonus round will begin. The Bonus game will be repeated in proportion to the number of triggering Strawberry symbols.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 94.39%, well below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€81 per spin.
Fruit Cocktail offers medium volatility, making it a less ideal match for our preferred slot machine strategies. We suggest pursuing the highest possible volatility when choosing slots.

media.caption: High paying symbols paytable in the Fruit Cocktail slot

Conclusion.text:
We do not recommend this low RTP, medium volatility fruit-themed slot.
Although the classic aesthetics of this slot may fill some players with nostalgia for years gone by, the RTP is simply too low to merit a recommendation.
Meanwhile, the moderate volatility will appeal less to mathematically-inclined players.

Theme and Storyline.text:
This slot is themed on a jungle adventure and cryptic temple.
Players arrive into the game through an immersive opening scene. They are Indiana Jones-like heroes traversing a challenging and overgrown landscape.
Players will then stumble on a mystical temple like those of Cambodia. Before them are gems and a haunting golden sculpture of Buddha. His green jewel eyes challenge players to win the right to pass into the majestic shrine.
Artistic license is definitely taken with the symbols, but the game delivers on its fantasy theme. Players will be happy to stay in this world until their thirst for adventure is satisfied.

media.caption: Big win in the Temple Tumble Megaways slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The game begins with a prologue animated in an edgy graphic novel style. The sketch-like figures and restrained colours set the tone for a dark adventure story.
The illustration of the temple pillars is impressively detailed and the ever-blowing mist in the background adds tension. The jungle foliage seems ominous with their roots crawling along the stone.
The reels land like stones after each spin, releasing small puffs of dust. Players will feel like they are decoding the secret to enter the temple.
Most fun are the free spin rounds when players plunge through the entrance. Inside, they’ll find menacing animal statues glowing in the shadows. The reels stand between players and an ornate likeness of Buddha, though he has a sinister vibe.
The music captures the mood of a climatic Indiana Jones scene. However, it only plays at transitional moments. This is refreshing and keeps the soundtrack novel.
Overall, the animation of this game is fantastic in its depth and detail. Players will definitely feel part of the story.

media.caption: The prologue animation is here for a better immersion into the slot's gameplay

Gameplay.text:
Temple Tumble Megaways is a six reel, six row slot. They use the popular Megaways system.
The Megaways system uses an Any Way Wins system which means that matching symbols in adjacent reels give the player a win. The number of symbols is randomised between one and six.
The cascade feature allows any winning symbols and the stones beside them to be destroyed so that new stones fall into place. This creates the opportunity for more back-to-back wins.

media.caption: Temple Tumble Megaways uses the cascade system
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols and appears on all reels except the first.
Players gain 6 free spins when all the non-symbol blocks in the main game are destroyed.
During the Free Spin Bonus game, players will find some of the non-symbol blocks are special as they hold Multipliers (x1, x2, or x3) or extra spins (+1, +2, or +3 spins). Destroying all symbols in the Bonus game awards the player another 3 free spins.

The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.05 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.
